Lo, batch processing is a craft wherein data, vast and manifold, is wrought in great heaps, known as "batches," not one by one, but in mighty throngs. Forsooth, 'tis most meet when volumes of matter must be shaped and sent forth. In a Java Spring project, the noble Spring Batch doth lend its aid, an open-source, light yet stalwart framework, to automate such toil.

Hark, here is a pattern, drawn from the hallowed scroll of Maven's `pom.xml`:

```xml
